r of Trinitarian theology and his groundbreaking work on Thomas Aquinas’ doctrine of complacent love as an analogy for the Holy Spirit’s eternal procession, no book has ever been published on this influential Canadian Jesuit, who set up centres around the world for the study of the thought of Bernard Lonergan, SJ (1904–84). Drawing on Crowe’s published works and archival material, Eades emphasizes how Crowe’s Trinitarian pneumatology modestly and creatively extended Lonergan’s theology of the Holy Spirit. Making use of Crowe’s own historical methodology, Eades looks for the emergence of new and significant questions about the Holy Spirit in Crowe’s works.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aHoly Spirit. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh  aBernard Lonergan.  aFrederick Crowe.  aHoly Spirit.  aJesuits.  aLonergan Research Institute.  aLonergan’s influence.  aTheology in Canada.  aTrinitarian.  acomplacentia.  apneumatology.  apsychological analogy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishz978311061074108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2019z9783110606508oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753235240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487532352423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487532352.jpg  a978-3-11-061074-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE C